Privacy Policy
Last updated:
3/5/2025
1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy ("Policy") outlines the practices of AirCodum ("we," "us," or "our") regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of information through our VS Code extension and associated mobile application (collectively, the "Service"). By utilizing our Service, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Policy.
2. Information Collection and Use
AirCodum is designed to operate without collecting, storing, or transmitting any personal data or usage information. All operations, including file transfers and VS Code control functionalities, are processed locally on your devices and within your local network.
3. Local Processing
The Service facilitates communication between the mobile application and the VS Code extension directly within your local network. No data is transmitted to external servers or third parties during this process.
4. Mobile Application Permissions
The AirCodum mobile application may request certain device permissions necessary for its core functionalities, such as access to device storage for file transfers or network access for communication with VS Code. These permissions are utilized solely for the intended purposes within your local environment and do not result in any data collection or transmission beyond your local network.
5. Third-Party Services
The Service does not integrate with or utilize any third-party services that would involve data transmission outside of your local network.
6. Children's Privacy
Our Service is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from children under 13. If you are aware of any data we may have collected from children under age 13, please contact us using the information provided in the Contact section of this Policy.
7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting of the updated Policy. We will notify users of any material changes via a prominent notice on our Service or through direct communication. Your continued use of the Service after any such changes constitutes your acceptance of the new Policy.
8. Contact Information
